FigureS5N

Load Data

library(gdata)
dataset <- read.delim("raw_data/FigureS5N.txt", stringsAsFactors = FALSE)

colnames(dataset) <- gsub("NHEJ.","Outcome", colnames(dataset))

dataset$genotype <- factor(gsub(" ","",dataset$genotype), levels = c("mCherry", "mCherry-ALC1"))
dataset$experiment <- factor(rep(paste0("exp", 1:(length(dataset$genotype)/length(levels(dataset$genotype)))), each= length(levels(dataset$genotype))))


kable(dataset, row.names = F)
genotype Outcome experiment
mCherry 26.05615 exp1
mCherry-ALC1 34.64230 exp1
mCherry 25.28045 exp2
mCherry-ALC1 34.79269 exp2
mCherry 23.08507 exp3
mCherry-ALC1 35.13055 exp3 
dataset$Offset <- NA
for(eid in levels(dataset$experiment)){
        dataset$Offset[dataset$experiment == eid] <- mean(dataset$Outcome[dataset$experiment == eid])
}

dataset$NormOutcome <- dataset$Outcome / dataset$Offset

dataset$Offset2 <- NA
for(gid in levels(dataset$genotype)){
        dataset$Offset2[dataset$genotype == gid] <- mean(dataset$NormOutcome[dataset$genotype == "mCherry"])

}

dataset$NormOutcome2 <- dataset$NormOutcome / dataset$Offset2


kable(dataset, row.names = F)
genotype Outcome experiment Offset NormOutcome Offset2 NormOutcome2

mCherry-ALC1 34.64230 exp1 30.34922 1.1414559 0.831096 1.3734344

dataplot$se <- aggregate(NormOutcome2 ~ genotype, data = dataset, FUN = function(x){ sd(x)/sqrt(length(x))})$NormOutcome2

dataplot$genotype <- factor(dataplot$genotype, levels = c("mCherry", "mCherry-ALC1"))

Linear Model

library(MASS)
library(DHARMa)
library(lme4)
library(lmerTest)
library(bbmle)
fit1 <- lm(NormOutcome2 ~ genotype, data = dataset)
print(summary(fit1))

Final Result

fit <- fit1

output <- coef(summary(fit))
#output <- output[grep("genotype", rownames(output)),]

rownames(output) <- gsub("genotype",   paste0(" ",levels(dataset$genotype)[1], " vs. "), rownames(output))


# suggested result table
kable(output, row.names = T)
Estimate Std. Error t value Pr(>|t|)
(Intercept) 1.0000000 0.0236064 42.36139 0.0000019
mCherry vs.mCherry-ALC1 0.4064607 0.0333845 12.17514 0.0002612 
write.table(output, file = "FigureS5N_Stats_Ref_mCherry.txt", quote = F, sep = "\t", row.names = T, col.names = NA)
# re-fit with mCherry-ALC1 reference
dataset$genotype <- relevel(dataset$genotype, ref = "mCherry-ALC1")

fit <- lm(NormOutcome2 ~ genotype, data = dataset)

output <- coef(summary(fit))
#output <- output[grep("genotype", rownames(output)),]

rownames(output) <- gsub("genotype",   paste0(" ",levels(dataset$genotype)[1], " vs. "), rownames(output))


# suggested result table
